definitions.definition: The state of being a member of a group or organization.
examples: The terms of membership agreement were vague.
He has memberships in clubs in three cities.

definitions.definition: The body of members of an organization.
examples: The memberships of the state chapters elect delegates to the national convention.

definitions.definition: The fact of being a member of a set .

main_definition: The state of being a member of a group or organization.
secondary_definitions: The body of members of an organization.
( mathematics ) The fact of being a member of a set .
